What is a server
A Server is a specialized computer or software system designed to provide services, resources, or data to other computers, known as clients, over a network.

What is the role of the domain name
Domain names provide human-readable addresses for websites and online services. Instead of typing a complex series of numbers(IP Adresses).

What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com
CNAME (Canonical Name) record 

What is the role of the web server
A web server is designed to host websites and deliver web pages to users' browsers upon request. It processes requests for HTML pages, images, scripts, and other web resources.

What is the role of the application server
An application server hosts and runs specific software applications or services. It provides a runtime environment for applications, enabling them to interact with databases, perform calculations, and deliver dynamic content to users.

What is the role of the database
A database plays a central role in storing, managing, and retrieving data in a structured and efficient manner.

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website
IP Adress

Issues with SPOF Includes:
.System Downtime:
If the component designated as the SPOF fails, the entire system can go offline. This downtime can disrupt services, cause loss of productivity, and negatively impact user experience.


.Limited Scalability: SPOFs can limit the system's ability to scale. Introducing redundancy and failover mechanisms often require additional complexity, making it challenging to scale the system seamlessly.



